gomodel:SYNGO_675  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Yotiao is a protein that interacts with the NMDA receptor subunit NR1 (Fig.3). The protein is membrane associated and enriched in postsynaptic densities obtained after biochemical fractionation of the rat brain (Fig.5). Immunolabeling of Yotiao and NR1 show colocalizing immunoreactivity in somatodendritic puncta in pyramidal neurons of the rat cerebral cortex (Fig.7).\n\n13/6/2017 Pim\n- The yotiao protein comes from the Akap9 gene. There is no reviewed rat sequence in Uniprot. There is a fragment (~350 aa) in Uniprot that bears the name Yotiao, but this seems to be a partial fragment. I selected full length Akap9 for annotation.\n- Paper shows (1) localization to PSD and (2) interaction with NR1 but does not show direct interaction with NR1 at the PSD. Therefore the evidenced term is PSD, and later a inferred annotation to 'extrinsic component of postsynaptic density membrane (GO:0099147)' will be added.. Experimental description: From M&M section:\n- The original human yotiao cDNA fragment, clone A1.7, was used as a hybridization probe to obtain from a 5 -Stretch Plus human brain cDNA phage library (Clontech) further clones (3-1, 9-1, 21-1, 25-1, and 25-2) that encompassed residues 138-1642 of the putative yotiao protein.\n-Brain immunohistochemistry was performed on Vibratome-cut 50 m floating brain sections from Sprague Dawley rats ( 6 weeks of age).\n-Subcellular fractions of whole rat brain were prepared as described (Huttner et al., 1983).\n\n10/8/2017 Pim\n- PPI is shown with human Yotiao and **unknown species** NR1 proteins." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_675" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

